From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Sat, 20 Jun 2026 11:51:47 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] xargs: inject logical I/O for an in-process brush builtin
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

xargs reads its items from stdin and writes diagnostics (`-t` traces, the
mutually-exclusive warning, errors), help/version text, and the no-command
`echo` output to stdout/stderr. Run as an in-process brush builtin those are
the ENGINE's process-global fd 0/1/2 (a control channel, a parent pipe, another
box's stream) — reading or writing them would steal/corrupt a neighbour's
bytes, the same data-corruption class the find `-files0-from -` seam fixed.

Carve a minimal `XargsIo` trait over the three logical streams and thread it
surgically through `do_xargs` -> `normalize_options` / `process_input` ->
`CommandBuilder::execute`, replacing the six process-global touchpoints:
`io::stdin()`, the `-t` `eprintln!`, the Echo `println!`, the warning
`eprintln!`, the help/version `print!`, and the final `Error:` `eprintln!`.
`StandardXargsIo` reproduces upstream behaviour (real stdin/stdout/stderr) so
`xargs_main` / `main.rs` stay byte-identical; the new `xargs_main_with_io`
entry is what the embedder calls. The commands xargs SPAWNS still inherit the
process fds via `Command`, exactly as `find -exec` does — in a box those are
the shell's logical fd 1/2. No behavior changes; every option preserved.

Re-expose `pub mod xargs;` in lib.rs (find-and-xargs library now).

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>
Claude-Session: https://claude.ai/code/session_01B5MwFcipu6iwqtMPPwFhXd
